The collection of weaponry at the State History Museum in Moscow is one of the largest in Russia. This album presents weapons made by Russian and European armorers, craftsmen of the North Caucasus, Iran, Turkey, India, China and Japan. Every piece reproduced in the album is accompanied by a detailed description.
